# Print-Ready HTML

Skill for producing HTML that prints correctly across browsers — preserving backgrounds, colors, and layout while suppressing browser-injected headers/footers.

---

## Default paper size

**Always use `Letter portrait` as the default paper size** unless the user specifies otherwise.

```css
@page {
  margin: 0;
  size: Letter portrait; /* DEFAULT — change only if user requests a different size or orientation */
}
```

Supported alternatives (use only when user requests):

| User request | `size` value |
|---|---|
| A4 | `A4 portrait` |
| A4 landscape | `A4 landscape` |
| Letter landscape | `Letter landscape` |
| Legal | `Legal portrait` |

---

## The core problem

Browsers strip background colors, gradients, and images by default when printing to save ink. Any design relying on backgrounds will appear blank without explicit overrides.

---

## Rules

### 1. Force color fidelity

```css
* {
  -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; /* Chrome, Safari, Edge */
  print-color-adjust: exact;         /* W3C standard */
}
```

Apply to `*`, `body`, and `.page` — the wildcard covers all children, but being explicit on key containers is safer.

---

### 2. Suppress browser auto headers/footers

The browser injects date, page title, URL, and page number into the page margins. Remove them with:

```css
@page {
  margin: 0;
}
```

> **Critical:** You cannot keep `@page` margins while hiding the browser headers/footers — they live in the same space. If you need breathing room, use padding on `body` instead.

---

### 3. Restore breathing room via body padding

Since `@page { margin: 0 }` removes all margin, compensate with body padding:

```css
body {
  padding: 10mm; /* 5mm = tight, 10mm = standard, 15mm = generous */
}
```

Use `mm` or `pt` units — they map cleanly to paper. Pixels don't.

---

### 4. Control page breaks

Prevent awkward mid-element splits:

```css
h2, h3        { page-break-after: avoid; }
.card, .section { page-break-inside: avoid; }
```

---

### 5. Prevent content overflow to the next page

Content overflowing onto an unwanted extra page is one of the most common print issues. Apply all of these together.

**Constrain the page container to exact paper dimensions:**

```css
.page {
  width: 215.9mm;      /* Letter width */
  max-height: 279.4mm; /* Letter height — subtract padding as needed */
  overflow: hidden;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

Paper height reference:

| Paper | Width | Height |
|-------|-------|--------|
| Letter portrait | 215.9mm | 279.4mm |
| A4 portrait | 210mm | 297mm |
| Letter landscape | 279.4mm | 215.9mm |
| A4 landscape | 297mm | 210mm |

**Strip any property that forces extra height:**

```css
@media print {
  body {
    min-height: unset;       /* NEVER use 100vh in print */
    height: auto;
  }
  * {
    min-height: unset !important; /* catch components that hardcode min-height */
  }
}
```

**Dynamically scale content down if it still overflows** — add before `</body>`:

```html
<script>
  window.addEventListener('load', () => {
    const page = document.querySelector('.page');
    if (!page) return;
    const paperHeightMm = 279.4; /* Letter — adjust for other paper sizes */
    const paddingMm = 20;        /* match your body padding (both sides) */
    const mmToPx = 96 / 25.4;
    const maxPx = (paperHeightMm - paddingMm) * mmToPx;
    if (page.scrollHeight > maxPx) {
      const scale = maxPx / page.scrollHeight;
      page.style.transform = `scale(${scale})`;
      page.style.transformOrigin = 'top left';
      page.style.width = `${100 / scale}%`;
    }
  });
</script>
```

**Font and spacing safety net** — reduce sizes when content is dense:

```css
@media print {
  body      { font-size: 10pt; }   /* reduce from 12pt if needed */
  p, li     { line-height: 1.4; }  /* tighter than screen default */
  .section  { margin-bottom: 4mm; }/* avoid large gaps eating height */
}
```

---

### 6. Declare paper size

Always declare paper size explicitly. Default to `Letter portrait` unless the user specifies otherwise:

```css
@page {
  margin: 0;
  size: Letter portrait; /* DEFAULT */
}
```

---

### 7. Hide screen-only elements

```css
nav, .sidebar, button, .no-print { display: none; }
```

Add `class="no-print"` to any element that should never appear in print.

---

### 8. Show link URLs (optional, for documents)

```css
a[href]::after {
  content: " (" attr(href) ")";
  font-size: 10pt;
  color: #666;
}
```

