## Chrome print dialog checklist

Even with correct CSS, Chrome has a per-print user toggle:

> **Print dialog → More settings → enable "Background graphics"**

CSS alone cannot force this on — the user controls it.

---

## Design rules summary

| Rule | Why |
|------|-----|
| Default to `Letter portrait` | Standard US paper size when user doesn't specify |
| Use `mm` or `pt` units in print styles | Pixels don't map cleanly to paper |
| Remove `box-shadow` on containers | Often renders poorly on paper |
| Remove `border-radius` on containers | Can look odd at print resolution |
| Avoid `min-height: 100vh` on body | Causes extra blank pages |
| Google Fonts work fine | Load before print render; no color impact |
| Gradients, pills, banners all print correctly | As long as `print-color-adjust: exact` is set |

---

## Diagnostics

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Colors/backgrounds missing | Missing `print-color-adjust: exact` | Add to `*`, `body`, `.page` |
| Browser date/title showing | Missing `@page { margin: 0 }` | Add inside `@media print` |
| Content touching paper edge | Missing body padding | `body { padding: 10mm }` |
| Extra blank page | `min-height: 100vh` or oversized element | Remove from print styles |
| Shadows/rounded corners look bad | Screen-only decoration in print | `box-shadow: none; border-radius: 0` |
| Backgrounds still missing after CSS fix | Chrome user toggle off | Print dialog → Background graphics |
| Page breaks mid-heading or mid-card | No break control | `page-break-after/inside: avoid` |
| Content overflows Letter page | Wrong paper size assumed | Confirm `size: Letter portrait` in `@page` |
| Content spills onto a second page | `.page` has no height cap | Set `max-height` to paper height and `overflow: hidden` |
| Second page appears even with no real content | `min-height: 100vh` or component `min-height` | Strip with `min-height: unset !important` in print styles |
| Content is cut off at the bottom | `overflow: hidden` too aggressive | Use the JS scale snippet to shrink content to fit instead |

---

## Pre-print checklist

- [ ] `print-color-adjust: exact` on `*`, `body`, `.page`
- [ ] `@page { margin: 0; size: Letter portrait; }` inside `@media print` (or user-specified size)
- [ ] `body { padding: 10mm }` inside `@media print`
- [ ] No `min-height: 100vh` on body in print styles
- [ ] `box-shadow: none` on containers in print styles
- [ ] `.page` has `max-height` set to paper height and `overflow: hidden`
- [ ] No `min-height` on any element in print styles (`unset !important`)
- [ ] Units use `mm` or `pt` where precision matters
- [ ] Page-break rules on headings and cards
- [ ] Screen-only elements hidden with `display: none`
- [ ] *(User)* Chrome → More settings → "Background graphics" enabled
- [ ] Tested with Ctrl/Cmd+P before delivery
